dcterms:creator: J. Gratch
R. Artstein
dcterms:description: The eDAIC dataset consists of semi-clinical interviews aimed at identifying mental health disorders such as anxiety, depression, and post-traumatic stress disorder. It includes audio recordings, eGeMAPS features, MFCC features, and deep audio representations from VGG-16, with each recording labeled by PHQ-8 and PCL-C scores.
dcterms:title: eDAIC

dcterms:creator: Y. Zhang
W. Hu
Q. Wu
dcterms:description: The DAIC-WOZ dataset is used for detecting depression from speech through an autoencoder model based on cepstrum separation. It serves as a training target for the model, utilizing original speech as input.
dcterms:title: DAIC-WOZ

dcterms:description: The TIMIT dataset is utilized for PTSD identification through a deep transfer learning approach. It provides various speech features that are combined using a deep belief network model.
dcterms:title: TIMIT
